Part 4: EGF / OGF analysis
======================================================================

  For odd n=2m+1: a(n) = sum over ODD j in [1, n-2] of j^{(n-j)/2} * j!
  For even n=2m: a(n) = sum over EVEN j in [2, n-2] of j^{(n-j)/2} * j!
  n=3 (parity 1): j values = [1], parities = [1]
  n=4 (parity 0): j values = [2], parities = [0]
  n=5 (parity 1): j values = [3, 1], parities = [1, 1]
  n=6 (parity 0): j values = [4, 2], parities = [0, 0]
  n=7 (parity 1): j values = [5, 3, 1], parities = [1, 1, 1]
  n=8 (parity 0): j values = [6, 4, 2], parities = [0, 0, 0]
  n=9 (parity 1): j values = [7, 5, 3, 1], parities = [1, 1, 1, 1]
  n=10 (parity 0): j values = [8, 6, 4, 2], parities = [0, 0, 0, 0]
  n=11 (parity 1): j values = [9, 7, 5, 3, 1], parities = [1, 1, 1, 1, 1]

